# 2p_ctf_walk_own_flag — host side. Plays the RED team. Stationary
# observer. The client (BLUE) walks back and forth across the BLUE
# (their own team's) flag at x=4160 to expose any stuck/collision
# behavior.
#
# This is the reproducer for the bug:
#   "the client appears to get stuck on their own flag in testing.
#    The server can pass through their own flag as expected."
#
# We need the host running the round so the client has a server to
# connect to. The shot_dump_tick sink emits per-mech pelvis pos every
# tick — host log will show mech=1 (the client) trajectory crossing
# x=4160. If the host believes the client moves smoothly and the
# client's own log shows the same particle stuck, that proves the
# divergence is on the client.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/host_walk_own_flag
network host 24017
name HostRed

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

at 60  shot t60_lobby
at 140 shot t140_round_start
at 200 shot t200_observer
at 260 shot t260_observer
at 320 shot t320_observer
at 400 shot t400_observer
at 700 end
